* Create IAM role
* Create Lambda function
* Add Python code
* Deploy & test



üöÄ Create S3 Bucket Using AWS Lambda (Python)

This project demonstrates how to create an S3 bucket using a Lambda function written in Python.

üìå Prerequisites

AWS Account

IAM role with required policies

Python 3.9 runtime support in Lambda

1Ô∏è‚É£ Create IAM Role for Lambda
Go to IAM ‚Üí Roles ‚Üí Create Role
Select AWS Service ‚Üí Lambda
Attach the following policies:
AmazonS3FullAccess ‚Üí Allows creating S3 bucket
AWSLambdaBasicExecutionRole ‚Üí Required for CloudWatch logs
Save role with name ‚Üí LambdaS3Role

2Ô∏è‚É£ Create Lambda Function
Go to AWS Lambda ‚Üí Create function
Select Author from scratch
Function name: lamdas3cr
Runtime: Python 3.9
Execution role: Choose LambdaS3Role (created earlier)
Click Create function

3Ô∏è‚É£ Add Python Code
Replace default Lambda code with the following:

import boto3

def lambda_handler(event, context):
    s3 = boto3.client('s3')

    # Must be globally unique bucket name
    bucket_name = "my-lambda-created-bucket-12345-shree"
    region = "ap-south-1"  # Mumbai region

    try:
        response = s3.create_bucket(
            Bucket=bucket_name,
            CreateBucketConfiguration={'LocationConstraint': region}
        )
        return {
            'statusCode': 200,
            'body': f"S3 Bucket '{bucket_name}' created successfully!"
        }

    except Exception as e:
        return {
            'statusCode': 500,
            'body': str(e)
        }

4Ô∏è‚É£ Deploy & Test

Click Deploy in Lambda console.
Change function timeout (optional):
Go to Configuration ‚Üí General configuration ‚Üí Edit
Set Timeout to 1 min
Go to Test ‚Üí Configure test event:

{
  "test": "s3bucket"
}
Click Test ‚Üí You should see success message.

Check S3 Console for the new bucket.


‚ö†Ô∏è Possible Errors

BucketAlreadyOwnedByYou ‚Üí You already have a bucket with the same name.
BucketAlreadyExists ‚Üí Someone else has already taken that bucket name (must be globally unique).
AccessDenied ‚Üí IAM role does not have s3:CreateBucket permission.
InvalidLocationConstraint ‚Üí Wrong region name. Use ap-south-1, us-east-1, etc.
